node.text:
EPIC video from Finns Beach Club! They’ve partnered with Bali Tourism Board, Wonderful Indonesia and Garuda Airlines with an incredible offer to get the world #backtobali ! 
When you buy a Back To Bali voucher, your initial payment TRIPLES in value to spend on food and drinks, accommodation and Finns Bali memberships during your next holiday to Bali, plus exclusive access to discounts on accommodation, adventures, dining experiences and more! 
Here’s the link for vouchers - these are 100% going to sell out so get in quick. https://finns.to/SagQ3
I’ve got mine - I’ll see you in Bali! 
Follow @finnsbeachclub for more info.

node.text:
Pressure 
The strongest souls of this world are those that have both felt immense pressure, and overcome it 
This Lion King didn’t get here by cowering away from opposition; even when it’s 20 to 1 
And even with help, that is why he is the King 
Video by © BBC Earth @bbcearth

node.text:
Canada's breathtaking spots via @mthiessen. 🌈 From natural landscapes to clean and modern cities, Canada is as picturesque as it gets when it comes to spectacular scenery. 🇨🇦

Swipe through and marvel at these incredible places! Save this post for reference when you visit Canada. 📝

Destinations in Canada
1-3. Niagara Falls, Ontario
4. Spirit Island, Alberta
5. Jasper, Alberta
6. Golden fields near Stony Plain, Alberta
7. Emerald Lake, British Columbia
8. Moraine Lake Road, Alberta
9. Lake Louise, Alberta
10. Edmonton, Alberta

Which one is your favorite? 👇

📸 @mthiessen 
📍 Canada

node.text:
A dust devil spotted by @rodrigoviverosphoto in Alto Las Vizcachas, Chile. 🇨🇱 Have you ever seen one in person? 😮

Also known as sand devils, dust devils are an interesting phenomena that usually show up under hot, clear-sky conditions with light winds. They're relatively small and brief whirlwinds that occur when a land surface heats rapidly, with much cooler air above it. The hot air then stretches and causes a spinning motion, similar to a tornado.🌪

📽 @rodrigoviverosphoto
📍 Alto Las Vizcachas, Chile
🎶 Howard Shore - One of the Dúnedain / "Evenstar" (feat. Isabel Bayrakdarian)
